Looking at your code sample I assume you are not using Spring Boot, which is the focus of the linked question.

What you need to do is wrapping your scheduled call into a [`RequestContextExecutor::execute`][1] call. For your example it would look like this:

``` java
@Override
public void execute(JobExecutionContext arg0) throws JobExecutionException {
    new RequestContextExecutor().execute(() -&gt; {
        new ODataScheduledFetch().execute();
    });
}
```

Depending on what you do inside your `ODataScheduledFetch::execute` call you might need to use the [`JwtBasedRequestContextExecutor`][2] (on CloudFoundry only).

----------

For a bit mor background:

All `*Accessor` classes (e.g. [`TenantAccessor`][3], [`DestinationAccessor`][4]) rely on a so called [`RequestContext`][5] to be available in the current Thread/Request. Such a `RequestContext` is created by the `RequestContextExecutor` as described above. 

To make your life easier in the usual use-case (which is on receiving Requests) we automatically load the [`RequestContextServletFilter`][6] which wraps all incoming Requests for you.

That is the reason why your code works in a Request but not scheduled.


  [1]: https://help.sap.com/doc/b579bf8578954412aea2b458e8452201/1.0/en-US/com/sap/cloud/sdk/cloudplatform/servlet/RequestContextExecutor.html
  [2]: https://help.sap.com/doc/b579bf8578954412aea2b458e8452201/1.0/en-US/com/sap/cloud/sdk/cloudplatform/security/JwtBasedRequestContextExecutor.html
  [3]: https://help.sap.com/doc/b579bf8578954412aea2b458e8452201/1.0/en-US/com/sap/cloud/sdk/cloudplatform/tenant/TenantAccessor.html
  [4]: https://help.sap.com/doc/b579bf8578954412aea2b458e8452201/1.0/en-US/com/sap/cloud/sdk/cloudplatform/connectivity/DestinationAccessor.html
  [5]: https://help.sap.com/doc/b579bf8578954412aea2b458e8452201/1.0/en-US/com/sap/cloud/sdk/cloudplatform/servlet/RequestContext.html
  [6]: https://help.sap.com/doc/b579bf8578954412aea2b458e8452201/1.0/en-US/com/sap/cloud/sdk/cloudplatform/servlet/RequestContextServletFilter.html

