If your objective is to create an endpoint with metrics for Prometheus a.k.a. OpenMetrics, you can use the [Prometheus JVM client][1] which is compatible with Spring framework.

Add dependency:

&lt;!-- language: lang-xml --&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
          &lt;groupId&gt;io.prometheus&lt;/groupId&gt;
          &lt;artifactId&gt;simpleclient_servlet&lt;/artifactId&gt;
          &lt;version&gt;0.16.0&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;

To collect metrics of requests, add as first filter in `web-app/WEB-INF/web.xml`:

&lt;!-- language: lang-xml --&gt;
      &lt;filter&gt;
        &lt;filter-name&gt;prometheusFilter&lt;/filter-name&gt;
        &lt;filter-class&gt;io.prometheus.client.filter.MetricsFilter&lt;/filter-class&gt;
        &lt;init-param&gt;
          &lt;param-name&gt;metric-name&lt;/param-name&gt;
          &lt;param-value&gt;webapp_metrics_filter&lt;/param-value&gt;
        &lt;/init-param&gt;
      &lt;/filter&gt;
      &lt;filter-mapping&gt;
        &lt;filter-name&gt;prometheusFilter&lt;/filter-name&gt;
        &lt;url-pattern&gt;/*&lt;/url-pattern&gt;
      &lt;/filter-mapping&gt;

To expose metrics as HTTP endpoint, add servlet:

&lt;!-- language: lang-xml --&gt;
      &lt;servlet&gt;
        &lt;servlet-name&gt;prometheus&lt;/servlet-name&gt;
        &lt;servlet-class&gt;io.prometheus.client.exporter.MetricsServlet&lt;/servlet-class&gt;
      &lt;/servlet&gt;
      &lt;servlet-mapping&gt;
        &lt;servlet-name&gt;prometheus&lt;/servlet-name&gt;
        &lt;url-pattern&gt;/metrics&lt;/url-pattern&gt;
      &lt;/servlet-mapping&gt;

After that you can see the metrics on the `/metrics` endpoint.

  [1]: https://github.com/prometheus/client_java

